    <h3 class=3D"faq-title faq-title-collapsed u-h4">bar to psi</h3>

   =20
   =20
        <div class=3D"faq-answer faq-answer-collapsed"><p><b>1 bar</b> =3D =
14.5037738 psi&nbsp;<br>
<b>1 psi </b>=3D 0.0689475729 bar<br>
</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><b>Examples:</b> <br>
Convert 2.5 bar to psi:&nbsp;<br>
2.5 bar =3D 2.5 =C3=97 14.5037738 psi =3D 36.2594345 psi</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Convert 78 psi to bar:&nbsp;<br>
78 psi =3D 78 =C3=97 0.0689475729 bar =3D 5.3789116862 bar</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><b>Conversion Table</b></p>
