   =20
   =20
        <div class=3D"faq-answer faq-answer-collapsed"><p><b>1 bar </b>=3D =
100000 Pa&nbsp;<br>
<b>1 Pa </b>=3D 0.00001 bar</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>For practical use, bar is often converted to kPa or MPa:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>1 bar =3D 100 kPa</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><p>1 bar =3D 0.1 MPa</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><b>Examples:</b><br>
Convert 1.8 bar to kPa:&nbsp;<br>
1.8 bar =3D 1.8 =C3=97 100 kPa =3D 180 kPa</p>
<p><br>
Convert 500 kPa to bar:&nbsp;<br>
500 kPa =3D 500 =C3=97 0.01 bar =3D 5 bar</p>
